snippet.textDisplay:
I'm really surprised by how well the movie has been received, honestly. When I saw it with my family, we all agreed it was a fun Agatha Christie-like murder mystery with some good ideas, but nothing incredible. To me it was a super average murder story, it had unbelievable plot conveniences, it barely gives you the illusion that you could solve the murder as an audience, and the revelation is nothing special. Basically, there's a cool twist in that Marta's investigating her own murder for a while, but otherwise it's one of those "meh" murder stories that you shouldn't think too much about or the whole plot crumbles entirely.
It gave me the feeling that I was looking at one of those christmas detective TV series, but with a big budget. It's nice, but a 6 or 7 out of 10 for me.
